news.title: Property Share receives SM REIT license from SEBI
news.para: The licence is registered to Property Share Investment Trust (PSIT). Property Share will become the investment manager to PSIT.

news.title: NBCC to develop Rs 15,000 crore Satellite Township in Srinagar
news.para: NBCC and SDA will develop the  Satellite Township at Rakh Gund Aksha, Bemina, Srinagar, which is spread over approximately 406 acres.

news.title: Deutsche Telekom Digital Labs leases 51,000 sq ft with WeWork in Gurugram
news.para: Deutsche Telekom Digital Labs has taken 51,000 sq ft at WeWork's DLF Cybercity in Gurugram, housing 700 work units. The lease has a 13-month lock-in period. WeWork India has been expanding its flexible workspaces across cities including Noida, Pune, Gurugram, and Chennai, reflecting the increasing demand for such spaces.

news.title: Grasim Industries reports net loss of Rs 521.2 million in Q1 FY25
news.para: The company reported a standalone net loss of 521.2 million rupees ($6.2 million) in the three months ending June 30 compared with a profit of 3.55 billion rupees a year ago, marking its second straight quarter of losses.

news.title: Hyderabad reports 48% growth in home registrations in July 2024
news.para: Hyderabad has set a record by registering over 46,000 homes in 2024, leading to a 40% year-on-year revenue surge. In July 2024 alone, the city registered homes worth Rs 4,266 crore, marking a 48% increase year-on-year with 7,124 units registered, up by 28% year-on-year.

news.title: New industrial policy to be unveiled soon: Puducherry minister
news.para: "Our intention is to encourage industries to come up in Puducherry so that jobs can be created for the educated youth," he said, and added that all aspects were being considered to ensure industrial development in the union territory.

news.title: Delhi civic body likely to conduct demolition drive in Bhalswa Dairy colony on August 12
news.para: In a public notice on Tuesday, the civic body gave a three-day ultimatum to defaulters to vacate the encroached premises. It said enforcement action will be taken against all illegal and unauthorised constructions after the expiry of the deadline and a demolition drive will be carried out.

news.title: MahaMetro acquires 50% land to build Nagpur metro phase-II
news.para: A total of 9 hectares land will be required for the Phase II development, out of which 36,626 sq m is govt land and 53,809 sq m is private, said MahaMetro managing director Sharavan Hardikar on Thursday during a media interaction. Hardikar also confirmed that work permission for 80% of the land has already been granted and the work has already begun.

news.title: DDA okays EWS flats at Narela for Kali Bari Marg jhuggi dwellers
news.para: The CPWD land was earlier designated for the expansion of the Ram Manohar Lohia (RML) Mother and Child Care Hospital. For the rehabilitation of the jhuggi dwellers here, the hospital, through the ministry of housing and urban affairs (MoHUA), earlier approached DDA to make housing available.

news.title: Bombay HC to decide on constituting SIT for razing of homes in Powai
news.para: “We don’t want to delay any further. Investigation has to start,” said Justices Revati Mohite-Dere and Prithviraj Chavan. The petition was by 28 residents seeking an FIR against Powai police, BMC officials and developer Hiranandani under IPC, including for voluntarily causing hurt and house trespass.

news.title: No decision on draft Delhi Master Plan 2041 yet: Housing ministry
news.para: In a written reply to a question, Union Minister of State for Housing and Urban Affairs Tokhan Sahu said the Delhi Development Authority (DDA) approved the proposal of the draft MPD-2041 on February 28, 2023.

news.title: Average rate on a 30-year mortgage falls to 6.47% in USA: Freddie Mac
news.para: Borrowing costs on 15-year fixed-rate mortgages, popular with homeowners refinancing their home loans, also fell this week, pulling the average rate down to 5.63% from 5.99% last week. A year ago, it averaged 6.34%, Freddie Mac said.

news.title: UP-RERA sends 250 possession related cases to courts of adjudicating officers
news.para: Sanjay Bhoosreddy, chairman, UP-RERA reviewed the status of compliance of the orders passed on the complaints of the allottees and realized that the promoters were trying to linger the delivery of possession to the allottees besides the orders for delivery of possession within a specified period of time.

news.title: Railways incurred Rs 835 crore loss due to ‘improper’ decision of land deal: CAG
news.para: CAG’s compliance audit report mentioned that the railway ministry in March 2018 gave “in principle” for an MoU between RLDA and IRCON and get lease premium upfront by transferring the development of land lease rights to the PSUs for generation of no-fare revenue for 2017-18.

news.title: Aadhar Housing Finance net profit jumps 37% to Rs Rs 200 crore in Q1 FY25
news.para: The total assets under management for the housing finance company stood at Rs. 21,726 crore, a 21% growth on year, from Rs. 17,947 crore

news.title: NGT files suo motu case over five-star hotel construction at Kaziranga
news.para: The development came days after the Assam government inked an agreement with the Tata Group to construct a five-star hotel in the vicinity of the UNESCO World Heritage site.

news.title: Blackstone to sell 33 crore units in Nexus Select Trust for nearly Rs 4,500 crore
news.para: According to sources, Blackstone plans to sell 33 crore units in Nexus Select Trust at a floor price of Rs 135 apiece. Block deal is likely to happen on Friday. Blackstone intends to monetise its investment through this block deal.

news.title: Birla Corporation's profit falls 45.4% to Rs 32.6 crore in Q1 FY25
news.para: Birla Corporation's revenue from operations was down 9 per cent to Rs 2,190.37 crore during the quarter under review. It was at Rs 2,407 crore in the corresponding period a year ago.

news.title: ED attaches Rs 113-crore worth assets of Krrish Realtech and Brahma City
news.para: A provisional order was issued under the Prevention of Money Laundering Act (PMLA) on August 6 to attach the properties worth Rs 113.03 crore in the case of Amit Katyal, Krrish Realtech Pvt. Ltd. and Brahma City Pvt. Ltd., the Enforcement Directorate said in a statement.
